data.chText: （皮肤上的）毛孔；（植物的）气孔；孔隙
data.enText: one of the very small holes in your skin that sweat can pass through; one of the similar small holes in the surface of a plant or a rock

data.chText: 仔细打量；审视；认真研读；审阅
data.enText: to look at or read sth very carefully

data.chText: 他的律师们正在审阅合同上的小号字。
data.enText: His lawyers are poring over the small print in the contract.

data.chText: 仔细打量；审视；认真研读；审阅
data.enText: to look at or read sth very carefully

data.chText: 他的律师们正在审阅合同上的小号字。
data.enText: His lawyers are poring over the small print in the contract.

tr: any small opening in the skin or outer surface of an animal
a minute epidermal pore in a leaf or stem through which gases and water vapor can pass
any tiny hole admitting passage of a liquid (fluid or gas)

example: Please focus on your studies and not on your hobbies

value.def: Your pores are the tiny holes in your skin.

example.ex: The size of your pores is determined by the amount of oil they produce.
example.tran: 毛孔大小取决于其出油多少。

value.def: The pores of a plant are the tiny holes on its surface.

example.ex: A plant's lungs are the microscopic pores in its leaves.
example.tran: 植物的肺就是其叶片上微细的气孔。

value.def: If you pore over or through information, you look at it and study it very carefully.

example.ex: We spent hours poring over travel brochures...
example.tran: 我们花了数小时仔细阅读旅游宣传册。

example.ex: It will take several more months to pore through the volumes of documents.
example.tran: 详细研究这大堆的文献还要多花好几个月的时间。

value.def: You can say that someone has a certain quality or emotion coming from every pore to emphasize the strength of that quality or emotion.

example.ex: She oozes sexuality from every pore...
example.tran: 她浑身上下每个毛孔都散发着性感。

example.ex: Waves of misery penetrated every pore.
